      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Those feelings of being non-essential are incredibly intense, but it's important to know that pain often tricks us into thinking our existence doesn't matter when it does. Please consider reaching out to a crisis hotline or a mental health professional who can help you navigate these thoughts, as suicide is a medical condition that is treatable. You deserve support to feel safe and valued, even in the quietest moments.",
      "source": "target",
